  <!-- SAVE INSTAGRAM VIDEOS ONLINE -->
  <section class="section-about" id="save-instagram-videos-online" aria-labelledby="videos-online-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="about-inner" aria-labelledby="videos-online-heading">
        <h2 id="videos-online-heading">Save Instagram Videos Online Free</h2>
        <p>DownReels lets you keep a personal offline copy of public Instagram videos — working as a dedicated Instagram video saver for PC, Mac, iPhone and Android without any app or software. Built specifically for standard Instagram video posts, it gives a faster, cleaner experience for the content type you actually need.</p>
        <p>An Instagram video downloader is a browser-based tool that lets you save public Instagram videos to your device for offline viewing — no account or app installation required.</p>

        <ul role="list" style="margin-top:16px;padding-left:0;list-style:none;display:grid;gap:10px;">
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E1306C" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg><span>Content creators saving inspiration from public accounts for personal offline reference</span></li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E1306C" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg><span>Anyone who wants to watch public Instagram videos offline without an internet connection</span></li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E1306C" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg><span>Users on slow or limited data connections who need a file saved locally</span></li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E1306C" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg><span>Anyone saving public videos for personal offline viewing on their own device</span></li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;"><svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#E1306C" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg><span>Anyone who wishes Instagram offered a simple save-to-device option</span></li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- HOW TO -->
  <section class="section-steps" id="how-to-save-instagram-video" aria-labelledby="steps-video-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 id="steps-video-heading">How to Save an Instagram Video</h2>
        <p>Three steps is all it takes. No account needed, no app to install — just a link and a click.</p>
      </div>
      <ol class="steps-list" aria-label="How to save an Instagram video">

        <li class="step-card">
          <div class="step-text-side">
            <h3>Step 1 &mdash; Copy the Video Link</h3>
            <ul class="step-bullets" role="list">
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Open Instagram and find the video post you want to save</span></li>
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Tap the three-dot menu at the top right of the post</span></li>
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Select &ldquo;Copy Link&rdquo; — the URL is now on your clipboard</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="step-img-side">
            <img src="/assets/images/steps/video-step1.webp" alt="Step 1 — showing Instagram video post three-dot menu with Copy Link option" class="phone-mockup" loading="lazy" width="400" height="700">
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="step-card reverse">
          <div class="step-text-side">
            <h3>Step 2 &mdash; Paste the Link</h3>
            <ul class="step-bullets" role="list">
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Come back to <strong>DownReels</strong></span></li>
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Tap the input box and paste your link using the Paste button or Ctrl+V</span></li>
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Make sure the full Instagram video URL is in the field</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="step-img-side">
            <img src="/assets/images/steps/video-step2.webp" alt="Step 2 — Phone screen showing Instagram video link pasted into DownReels input box" class="phone-mockup" loading="lazy" width="400" height="700">
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="step-card">
          <div class="step-text-side">
            <h3>Step 3 &mdash; Save the Video</h3>
            <ul class="step-bullets" role="list">
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Click the <strong>DOWNLOAD</strong> button and wait just a moment</span></li>
              <li><span class="bullet-text">A thumbnail preview appears with quality options below it</span></li>
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Choose <strong>Download HD</strong> and the MP4 saves to your device</span></li>
              <li><span class="bullet-text">Find it in your Downloads folder — ready to watch offline</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="step-img-side">
