  <!-- IPHONE -->
  <section class="section-device-guides bg-alt" id="how-to-save-instagram-video-iphone" aria-labelledby="iphone-video-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 id="iphone-video-heading">How to Save Instagram Videos on iPhone (to Camera Roll)</h2>
        <p>Save your Instagram videos directly to your iPhone camera roll — in seconds, with no app needed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="device-guides-inner">
        <article class="device-guide-block" aria-labelledby="iphone-video-steps-heading">
          <h3 id="iphone-video-steps-heading">iPhone Steps — Safari Browser</h3>
          <p>Open <strong>Safari</strong> on your iPhone and go to <strong>DownReels</strong>. Open Instagram, find the video, tap the three-dot menu and tap <strong>Copy Link</strong>. Return to DownReels, paste the link and tap Download. The video saves to your Files app. To move it to your camera roll, open <strong>Files</strong>, press and hold the video file, then tap <strong>Save Video</strong> — it appears in Photos under Recents instantly. <a href="#faq-video-4" style="color:var(--pink);">See full device save locations in our FAQ.</a></p>
        </article>
        <article class="device-guide-block" aria-labelledby="iphone-chrome-heading">
          <h3 id="iphone-chrome-heading">Using Chrome on iPhone</h3>
          <p>Chrome on iPhone works identically — open DownReels, paste your Instagram video link, tap Download. The file saves to your Files app Downloads folder. From there, press and hold the file and tap <strong>Save Video</strong> to add it to your iPhone camera roll.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ANDROID -->
  <section class="section-device-guides" id="how-to-save-instagram-videos-android" aria-labelledby="android-video-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 id="android-video-heading">How to Save Instagram Videos on Android (to Gallery)</h2>
        <p>Save public Instagram videos straight to your Android gallery — no app install, no account needed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="device-guides-inner">
        <article class="device-guide-block" aria-labelledby="android-chrome-heading">
          <h3 id="android-chrome-heading">Android Steps — Chrome Browser</h3>
          <p>Open <strong>Chrome</strong> on your Android phone and visit <strong>DownReels</strong>. Copy the Instagram video link from the three-dot menu and paste it into the tool. Tap Download and the MP4 file saves to your <strong>Downloads</strong> folder. It appears automatically in your <strong>Gallery app</strong> under Downloads — no extra steps needed.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="device-guide-block" aria-labelledby="android-gallery-heading">
          <h3 id="android-gallery-heading">Find Your Saved Video on Android</h3>
          <p>On Android, saved Instagram videos appear in two places: your <strong>Downloads folder</strong> (open Files app → Downloads) and your <strong>Gallery app</strong> (look for the Downloads album). You can move the video to any other album from Gallery by pressing and holding the file and tapping Move. <a href="#faq-video-4" style="color:var(--pink);">See full device save locations in our FAQ.</a></p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- KEY FEATURES -->
  <section class="section-features" id="key-features-video" aria-labelledby="video-features-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 id="video-features-heading">Key Features of the Instagram Video Saver</h2>
        <p>Built for one job — saving public Instagram videos in HD, clean and fast — and doing it better than tools that try to do everything at once.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li class="feature-row">
          <div class="feature-text-side">
            <span class="feature-tag">Quality</span>
            <h3>HD Video Quality</h3>
            <p>Instagram video posts are stored at the resolution the creator chose when uploading — square, portrait, or widescreen, up to Full HD where the original supports it. What you save through DownReels keeps that same quality level Instagram holds for public viewing, with no extra processing step on our end.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="feature-row">
          <div class="feature-text-side">
            <span class="feature-tag">Clean</span>
            <h3>Original Quality, Unchanged</h3>
            <p>The file you save keeps the original quality of the public post — the same resolution and format shown on Instagram. Just a clean MP4 file ready for offline viewing.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="feature-row">
          <div class="feature-text-side">
            <span class="feature-tag">Speed</span>
            <h3>Fast &amp; Easy</h3>
            <p>Paste a link, click download — your video is ready in seconds. There are no redirect pages, no countdown timers, no captcha loops and no sign-up forms standing between you and your file. The result appears as a thumbnail preview with a single download button — nothing to figure out.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="feature-row">
          <div class="feature-text-side">
            <span class="feature-tag">Privacy</span>
            <h3>No Login Required</h3>
            <p>You never need to sign into Instagram or share any personal details. DownReels works entirely without authentication — just the video link is enough. No username, no password, no permission needed from anyone.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="feature-row">
          <div class="feature-text-side">
            <span class="feature-tag">Free</span>
            <h3>Free to Use</h3>
            <p>No sign-up and no account needed. The tool is free to use for keeping your own personal offline copies.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>


